name: Burn the Satay
description: Satay (/ˈsɑːteɪ/ SAH-tay, in USA also /ˈsæteɪ/ SA-tay), or Sate, in Indonesian and Malay spelling, is a Southeast Asian dish consisting of seasoned, skewered and grilled meat, served with a sauce. The earliest preparations of satay are believed to have originated in Javanese cuisine, but have spread to almost all parts of Indonesia, where satay has become a national dish.
